amatrix.opencl bundles third-party header files so that the package can be
compiled on any platform without the OpenCL or CLBlast development packages
being installed. All device libraries are resolved at run time via
dlopen()/LoadLibrary(); none of the bundled headers are linked and no
third-party source code is compiled into the package binary.

